You need to examine the hardware to determine if the processor supports virtualization.Which command can be used to display the status of virtualization support?
A)  cpustat
B)  cpuinfo
C)  lscpu
D)  brcxpu
C
C. The lscpu command shows statistics about the CPU that include architecture, cache,speed, and other information. Among the other options, cpuinfo is not a command butrather the file /proc/cpuinfo contains the same information as lscpu. The other optionsare not valid commands.
